article.headline: Siena 91, Marist 85
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Alex Franklin had 19 points and 10 rebounds, Ryan Rossiter had 16 points and nine rebounds, and Kyle Downey had 15 points to lead Siena to a 91-85 overtime victory over Marist on Thursday night. Downey started the extra session with a layup after a missed free throw by Franklin, and Downey followed that with a steal and layup. Ronald Moore then hit a 3-pointer to give the Saints (13-5, 7-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) a commanding 84-76 lead midway through the overtime. R.J. Hall responded with a 3 from the left corner for Marist with 1:22 left to cut the lead to 85-80, but Siena made six free throws in the final 64 seconds to hold on. Ryan Schneider had 19 points, 13 rebounds and three blocks to lead Marist (7-12, 3-4).
